\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Singular Cohomology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 be a ring and 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 is a graded 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module, then we set 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{Hom}_{R}(M,N)_{\text{gr}}$
\end_inset

 to be the graded 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module whose homogeneous component in degree 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{n}:=\text{Hom}_{R}(M_{n},N)$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $(M,d)$
\end_inset

 is a chain complex over 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 is considered a graded 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module and 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 is considered a graded endomorphism 
\begin_inset Formula $d\colon M\to M$
\end_inset

 of degree 
\begin_inset Formula $-1$
\end_inset

, then we obtain a cochain complex over 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 given by 
\begin_inset Formula $(\text{Hom}_{R}(M,N)_{\text{gr}},d_{*})$
\end_inset

, where if 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\in\text{Hom}_{R}(M_{n-1},N)$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{*}(\psi)=\psi\circ d\in\text{Hom}_{R}(M_{n},N)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

In particular, we obtain a cochain complex 
\begin_inset Formula $(\text{Hom}_{R}(S(X),N)_{\text{gr}},\partial_{*})$
\end_inset

 called the 
\series bold
singular
\series default
 
\series bold
cochain complex of
\series default
 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 
\series bold
over 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset


\series default
 
\series bold
with values in 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset


\series default
.
 Elements in 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{n}(X)^{\lor}$
\end_inset

 are called 
\series bold
singular 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-cochains 
\series default
and the 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

th cohomology, called the 
\series bold
singular cohomology of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 over 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset


\series default
, is denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{\text{sing}}^{n}(X,R)$
\end_inset

.
 For notational purposes, we denote 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta:=\partial_{\text{gr}}^{\lor}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $S^{n}(X,R):=S_{n}(X,R)^{\lor}$
\end_inset

.
 We can work out 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

 explicitly as follows: if 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\in S^{n}(X)$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta(\psi)\in S^{n+1}(X)$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\delta(\psi)(\sigma)=\psi(\partial(\sigma))=\sum_{i}(-1)^{i}\psi(\sigma_{i})
\]

\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma\in S_{n+1}(X)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

